01:27.671 --> 01:28.923
(MEN WHOOPING)

01:30.591 --> 01:31.592
(CLAMORING)

01:34.678 --> 01:36.351
(MEN SCREAMING INDISTINCTLY)

01:46.565 --> 01:47.942
(MEN WHOOPING)

01:51.528 --> 01:52.529
(HORSE NEIGHS)

01:54.823 --> 01:55.824
(MAN GRUNTS)

02:00.412 --> 02:02.756
(MEN SCREAMING INDISTINCTLY)

02:03.540 --> 02:05.463
Najid, cut the horses loose!

02:07.711 --> 02:08.928
(HORSE NEIGHING)

02:17.012 --> 02:18.730
(ALL SCREAMING INDISTINCTLY)

02:48.919 --> 02:50.796
(GROANING)

02:52.839 --> 02:54.091
(GRUNTING)

02:57.386 --> 02:59.059
We have to turn back.

02:59.179 --> 03:01.273
We have been riding for six months.

03:01.431 --> 03:03.274
And we've lost 20 men.

03:03.433 --> 03:04.730
But we survived.

03:04.851 --> 03:06.694
Yes. By chance.

03:06.812 --> 03:10.112
Any one of us could have met that same fate.

03:10.273 --> 03:12.275
We were the strongest.

03:12.609 --> 03:14.282
Remember why you're here.

03:14.444 --> 03:18.199
In the West, we would be enemies,
and I would have to kill you.

03:18.615 --> 03:20.117
At least here, we have a common goal.

03:20.283 --> 03:21.409
RIZZETTI: Oh, yes.

03:21.493 --> 03:23.086
This black powder.

03:23.662 --> 03:25.585
It turns air into fire.

03:26.123 --> 03:28.376
And kills a dozen men at one time.

03:28.458 --> 03:30.381
It is the weapon of our dreams.

03:30.460 --> 03:31.962
And what if it's just a myth?

03:32.629 --> 03:34.973
Men have sent word that it's real.

03:35.090 --> 03:36.262
And those men are dead.

03:36.341 --> 03:37.718
And we are next.

03:38.301 --> 03:39.678
We have no maps,

03:39.803 --> 03:41.146
no medicine

03:41.263 --> 03:42.389
and no food.

03:42.973 --> 03:44.145
No one is going back.

03:45.058 --> 03:48.187
We take inventory of what we have left

03:48.353 --> 03:50.481
and finish what we started.

03:50.564 --> 03:52.658
TOVAR: There's not much here.

03:53.316 --> 03:54.693
The moon is strong.

03:54.818 --> 03:56.820
When the horses are fresh, we move.

03:56.903 --> 03:58.780
- To where?
- WILLIAM: North.

03:59.364 --> 04:02.413
If they keep after us,
we'll kill them in the mountains.

04:02.534 --> 04:03.911
The magnet.

04:06.163 --> 04:07.710
Too heavy.

04:07.831 --> 04:08.957
- TOVAR: Useless.
- I'll have it.

04:11.001 --> 04:12.127
It's all yours.

04:12.878 --> 04:13.879
(MAGNET THUDS)

04:17.089 --> 04:20.970
Amigo, only you would carry
a stupid magnet through the desert.

04:21.052 --> 04:22.645
I can use it to make a compass.

04:25.348 --> 04:27.521
Rizzetti won't make it.

04:28.268 --> 04:30.521
The wound is festering.

04:30.687 --> 04:32.109
We'll be dragging a corpse.

04:32.189 --> 04:34.283
I heard that.

04:35.108 --> 04:37.361
He's earned the right to die where he wants.

04:39.362 --> 04:40.909
I've been left for dead twice.

04:41.531 --> 04:43.158
- It was bad luck.
- For who?

04:43.241 --> 04:44.959
- The people who left me.
- (TOVAR CHUCKLES)

04:45.535 --> 04:46.957
Maybe Rizzetti's right.

04:51.875 --> 04:53.218
(CREATURE SCREECHING)

05:10.811 --> 05:12.108
Where are they?

05:18.193 --> 05:19.570
- (CREATURE GROWLING)
- (GASPS)

05:23.448 --> 05:24.495
(GASPS)

05:24.616 --> 05:25.868
Hill tribes?

05:26.576 --> 05:27.873
It's no man.

05:29.454 --> 05:30.876
(WHISPERS) Then what is it?

05:31.414 --> 05:34.714
Whatever it is, it's hunting.

05:36.336 --> 05:37.428
(CREATURE GROWLING)

05:44.219 --> 05:45.266
(PANTING)

05:45.804 --> 05:47.431
- What was that?
- I don't know.

05:48.181 --> 05:49.603
I took its hand.

05:49.724 --> 05:52.102
- TOVAR: We need to move.
- WILLIAM: Agreed.

05:52.227 --> 05:53.479
I'll take the hand with us.

05:53.603 --> 05:54.855
What the hell for?

05:55.772 --> 05:58.150
So someone can tell me what I just killed.

06:07.617 --> 06:08.994
(HORSE SNORTS)

06:10.829 --> 06:12.126
(HORSES APPROACHING)

06:14.624 --> 06:16.968
TOVAR: Persistent bastards, aren't they?

06:17.669 --> 06:20.639
We'll take the rise, make a stand there.

06:21.298 --> 06:24.472
What a long shitting way to go to die.

06:28.805 --> 06:29.806
(MEN WHOOPING)

06:45.572 --> 06:46.744
(MEN SCREAMING INDISTINCTLY)

07:11.640 --> 07:13.142
Mother of God.

07:13.266 --> 07:14.688
(MAN SPEAKS IN MANDARIN)

07:20.231 --> 07:21.278
(SWORDS DRAWING)

07:49.970 --> 07:52.814
(IN ENGLISH)
I have no need to go down fighting.

07:53.056 --> 07:54.399
Agreed.

07:55.433 --> 07:58.403
I say we take our chances
with the gents in front of us.

07:58.561 --> 08:01.064
I haven't surrendered in a while, eh?

08:03.191 --> 08:05.114
It'll come back to you.

08:12.283 --> 08:14.706
Follow my lead, we'll be fine.

08:15.370 --> 08:16.872
Of course, my friend.

08:17.038 --> 08:18.711
Where you go, I follow.

08:18.790 --> 08:20.713
You're doing such a great job already.

08:25.630 --> 08:27.132
(SOLDIER SCREAMING IN MANDARIN)

08:39.852 --> 08:40.945
(CONTINUES SCREAMING)

09:02.417 --> 09:04.135
(IN ENGLISH) They know what it is.

09:04.210 --> 09:05.632
And they don't look happy to see it.

09:06.212 --> 09:08.465
All the more reason
to get the hell out of here.

09:08.590 --> 09:10.513
Our weapons are on that table.

09:12.302 --> 09:14.145
Have you lost your mind?

09:14.220 --> 09:16.643
I can take out the guards
on the perimeter with my bow.

09:16.806 --> 09:18.433
You cut the legs out from under the officers.

09:18.600 --> 09:21.149
I must confess, this is not my favorite plan.

09:21.227 --> 09:23.571
LIN: Where was this found?

09:26.149 --> 09:27.822
You speak English.

09:28.276 --> 09:29.493
Fantastic.

09:32.781 --> 09:34.499
Where was this found?

09:35.283 --> 09:37.001
It wasn't found.

09:37.577 --> 09:38.829
It was taken.

09:38.912 --> 09:41.210
That thing killed three men
before we took it down.

09:41.414 --> 09:42.415
Where?

09:43.374 --> 09:44.842
Two days' ride.

09:45.001 --> 09:47.550
North, in the mountains.

09:48.088 --> 09:50.557
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

10:04.354 --> 10:06.573
(IN ENGLISH) Two of you, you did this?

10:06.731 --> 10:08.574
Well... (STUTTERS)

10:08.650 --> 10:09.902
I killed it.

10:10.026 --> 10:11.403
Alone?

10:14.697 --> 10:16.165
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

10:20.620 --> 10:22.338
(IN ENGLISH) Tell me how.

10:23.164 --> 10:24.711
A swing of the sword.

10:24.833 --> 10:26.881
The hand, it came away clean.

10:27.585 --> 10:29.929
The beast fell back into a chasm.

10:30.505 --> 10:32.098
Why are you here?

10:32.215 --> 10:33.933
We came to trade.

10:34.050 --> 10:36.018
We were ambushed.

10:36.970 --> 10:38.187
(SPEAKS IN MANDARIN)

10:42.559 --> 10:43.560
(GRUNTING)

10:50.108 --> 10:51.234
(IN ENGLISH) You are soldiers.

10:54.737 --> 10:56.080
(SPEAKS IN MANDARIN)

10:59.242 --> 11:00.243
(SIGHS)

11:02.036 --> 11:03.037
Mmm.

12:04.724 --> 12:05.976
(DRUMS BEATING)

12:22.867 --> 12:24.619
(IN ENGLISH) Are you killing us, sister?

12:24.744 --> 12:26.838
Two lost travelers?

12:27.830 --> 12:29.753
(SPEAKING IN SPANISH)

12:31.668 --> 12:33.136
(IN ENGLISH) I think she'd like that.

12:34.837 --> 12:38.432
If it is death, my dear,
we need time to pray.

12:39.133 --> 12:40.225
I'm trying here.

12:42.011 --> 12:44.810
Sister, I know a siege when I see one.

12:45.473 --> 12:47.976
What comes at you so hard
you need a wall like this?

12:48.101 --> 12:49.899
What the hell did we kill out there?

12:50.019 --> 12:51.521
STRATEGIST WANG: Tao Tei.

12:52.188 --> 12:54.532
You killed a Tao Tei scout.

12:54.607 --> 12:55.984
You killed it alone.

12:56.609 --> 12:57.826
You're correct.

12:57.902 --> 12:59.324
We are under siege.

13:00.029 --> 13:02.703
But we did not expect the attack
for another nine days.

13:02.865 --> 13:05.038
TOVAR: Attack? Tao Tei.

13:05.660 --> 13:07.412
What the hell is a Tao Tei?

13:07.537 --> 13:09.790
Many things about your story have importance.

13:10.373 --> 13:11.750
You are not to die today.

13:17.714 --> 13:20.388
- (SPEAKS IN MANDARIN)
- (KEYS RATTLE)

13:47.577 --> 13:48.874
(WHIRRING)

13:55.251 --> 13:57.094
(SOLDIER SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

14:14.854 --> 14:15.855
(MAN GRUNTING)

14:39.545 --> 14:41.092
(SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

14:42.673 --> 14:44.016
(SOLDIER GRUNTS)

14:59.357 --> 15:01.155
(METAL CREAKING)

15:08.449 --> 15:09.666
(SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

15:37.895 --> 15:39.397
(MAN SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)

15:56.581 --> 15:58.834
(IN ENGLISH) The black are the foot soldiers.

15:59.125 --> 16:00.126
And the red?

16:00.293 --> 16:01.419
Those are the archers.

16:18.186 --> 16:19.904
And the blue?

16:20.062 --> 16:21.484
They're all women.

16:21.647 --> 16:22.819
What the hell do they do?

16:27.361 --> 16:28.658
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

16:37.288 --> 16:39.040
(IN ENGLISH) Look at this army.

16:40.124 --> 16:41.876
Have you ever seen anything like this?

16:41.959 --> 16:43.586
Incredible.

16:48.966 --> 16:50.434
(SPEAKS IN MANDARIN)

17:03.564 --> 17:05.362
(IN ENGLISH) They look nervous.

17:06.442 --> 17:09.241
(SIGHS) It's a big wall to be so nervous.

17:22.333 --> 17:23.630
(TAO TEI SCREECHING)

17:27.547 --> 17:29.174
Do you hear it?

17:31.842 --> 17:33.890
(TAO TEI SCREECHING)

17:36.639 --> 17:37.640
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

17:39.976 --> 17:41.273
(DRUMS BEATING)

17:51.862 --> 17:53.535
(MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

18:00.997 --> 18:01.998
(MAN GRUNTS)

18:16.762 --> 18:18.355
(TAO TEI SCREECHING)

18:29.942 --> 18:31.364
(SCREECHING)

18:40.578 --> 18:42.626
(SCREECHES AND GROWLS)

19:06.646 --> 19:07.647
(SCREAMING)

19:13.903 --> 19:14.950
(GRUNTS)

19:23.329 --> 19:24.751
(SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)

19:29.126 --> 19:30.594
(GRUNTING)

19:35.299 --> 19:36.346
(SCREAMING)

19:38.594 --> 19:40.062
(TAO TEI SCREECHING)

19:48.229 --> 19:49.321
(WHIRRING)

20:02.159 --> 20:04.412
(IN ENGLISH) William, over there.

20:06.080 --> 20:07.923
Why isn't he tied up?

20:09.625 --> 20:10.877
There's our escape.

20:18.342 --> 20:19.810
(SCREECHING)

20:28.811 --> 20:30.563
(GROWLS)

20:32.356 --> 20:35.075
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

20:53.836 --> 20:54.837
(GROWLS)

21:01.343 --> 21:02.686
(GROWLING)

21:19.111 --> 21:20.704
(DRUMS BEATING)

21:30.456 --> 21:32.003
(TAO TEI SCREECHING)

21:36.712 --> 21:38.305
- (GROWLS)
- (SCREAMS)

21:41.550 --> 21:42.972
- (SCREAMS)
- (IN ENGLISH) We need to move!

21:43.052 --> 21:44.679
We need to move or we die!

21:46.972 --> 21:48.269
(SOLDIER SCREAMING)

21:51.143 --> 21:53.066
(SOLDIER SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

21:58.067 --> 21:59.364
(GROWLING)

22:02.696 --> 22:03.697
(IN ENGLISH) Go, go!

22:05.407 --> 22:06.533
Go and fight!

22:09.537 --> 22:11.539
- (SOLDIER SCREAMING)
- (GRUNTS)

22:12.915 --> 22:14.758
- (SCREAMING)
- Cut me loose!

22:18.546 --> 22:19.547
Fight or run?

22:19.630 --> 22:20.631
Run where?

22:20.881 --> 22:21.882
(SCREAMING)

22:26.053 --> 22:28.226
- (GRUNTS)
- WILLIAM: Aim for the eyes!

22:31.725 --> 22:32.726
(GRUNTS)

22:35.187 --> 22:36.609
- (GRUNTS)
- (GASPS)

22:49.410 --> 22:50.411
(GROWLS)

22:52.204 --> 22:53.296
(SOLDIERS SCREAMING)

22:59.003 --> 23:00.004
(GROWLING)

23:01.422 --> 23:02.469
(SCREECHING)

23:07.636 --> 23:08.637
TOVAR: William!

23:14.310 --> 23:15.311
(GRUNTING)

23:17.438 --> 23:18.485
(SCREECHING)

23:27.323 --> 23:28.324
(GROWLS)

23:35.289 --> 23:37.087
TOVAR: Hey! Bitch!

23:39.084 --> 23:40.085
(SNARLING)

23:45.716 --> 23:46.717
(SCREECHES)

23:50.179 --> 23:51.351
(SOLDIER SCREAMING)

23:53.015 --> 23:54.312
TOVAR: William.

23:54.433 --> 23:55.810
I need a shot.

24:03.859 --> 24:05.452
(SCREECHES)

24:12.826 --> 24:13.827
(SHRILL CRY)

24:43.399 --> 24:45.697
What god made those things?

24:46.694 --> 24:48.537
None that we know.

25:06.505 --> 25:08.223
Think they'll hang us now?

25:08.382 --> 25:10.430
I could use the rest.

25:22.396 --> 25:23.397
(GRUNTS)

25:35.743 --> 25:37.916
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

25:38.037 --> 25:39.755
(IN ENGLISH)
You've earned General Shao's praise.

25:39.872 --> 25:41.419
Will they come back?

25:41.540 --> 25:42.541
Yes.

25:43.125 --> 25:45.753
SHAO: All we can do is prepare.

25:47.004 --> 25:48.130
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

26:09.693 --> 26:10.819
(DOOR OPENS)

26:15.074 --> 26:16.451
(DOOR CLOSES)

26:19.119 --> 26:20.792
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

26:44.520 --> 26:46.113
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

27:20.264 --> 27:21.937
MAN: (IN ENGLISH) Who are you?

27:25.561 --> 27:26.904
(PANTING)

27:27.521 --> 27:29.023
Easy.

27:31.942 --> 27:33.910
I'm Ballard. Hmm?

27:35.070 --> 27:36.242
William.

27:37.072 --> 27:38.494
This is Tovar.

27:39.575 --> 27:41.418
BALLARD: What are you doing here?

27:42.494 --> 27:44.542
We came looking for black powder.

27:44.621 --> 27:46.874
I bet you did.

27:46.957 --> 27:49.710
I came with mercenaries for the same thing.

27:49.793 --> 27:51.420
Twenty-five years ago.

27:52.212 --> 27:53.384
And did you find it?

27:53.547 --> 27:56.676
Finding it and leaving with it alive
are two different things.

28:00.095 --> 28:03.690
You saved the west turret.
That was extremely diplomatic.

28:03.765 --> 28:05.733
We weren't being diplomatic.

28:05.809 --> 28:07.527
We were trying to stay alive.

28:10.147 --> 28:12.775
- You smell like animals.
- Thank you.

28:18.322 --> 28:19.665
Clean up

28:20.532 --> 28:22.330
and they'll feed you.

28:22.576 --> 28:23.577
(DOOR OPENS)

28:24.453 --> 28:26.547
- (DOOR CLOSES)
- He knows where the powder is.

28:28.123 --> 28:29.796
Then why is he still here?

28:30.584 --> 28:32.086
He needs help getting out?

28:32.711 --> 28:33.712
Right.

28:34.713 --> 28:36.431
We play our part,

28:36.548 --> 28:39.518
take the powder and go home.

28:40.844 --> 28:42.391
I didn't sign up for this.

28:42.512 --> 28:43.559
Which part?

28:44.765 --> 28:47.484
Well, all of it. But mostly the monsters.

28:48.477 --> 28:49.774
There's a lot of them.

28:53.148 --> 28:55.196
We really do smell.

29:07.746 --> 29:09.123
(ALL APPLAUDING)

29:27.474 --> 29:30.398
General Shao welcomes you as honored guests

29:30.519 --> 29:34.695
of the Nameless Order and thanks you
for your skill and courage.

29:37.109 --> 29:40.363
We are honored to be honored.

29:42.656 --> 29:44.158
Is that the best you've got?

29:44.283 --> 29:46.035
- (CLEARS THROAT)
- (SCOFFING)

29:48.245 --> 29:49.371
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

30:01.300 --> 30:04.891
LIN: (IN ENGLISH) Commander Chen
thinks your bow is not worthy of your skill.

30:05.470 --> 30:07.848
Tell him there's no better weapon here.

30:07.931 --> 30:11.731
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

30:11.810 --> 30:12.902
(ALL LAUGH)

30:15.230 --> 30:17.028
(SHAO SPEAKING)

30:19.818 --> 30:21.240
(ALL CHEERING)

30:25.782 --> 30:27.580
(IN ENGLISH) They wish to see you shoot.

30:28.076 --> 30:29.077
In here?

30:29.202 --> 30:31.751
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

30:33.248 --> 30:34.340
(IN ENGLISH) What was that?

30:34.458 --> 30:35.675
LIN: He thinks you have fear.

30:36.835 --> 30:38.508
Too many people.

30:41.798 --> 30:43.095
Get one of the cups.

30:43.258 --> 30:44.510
- Now?
- Get one of the cups.

30:44.593 --> 30:45.594
I want to eat.

30:50.057 --> 30:51.149
(SLURPS)

30:53.643 --> 30:54.644
You remember how to do this?

30:54.770 --> 30:56.989
- Last time didn't go so good.
- We were drunk.

30:57.773 --> 30:58.774
How high?

30:58.940 --> 31:01.784
Ten yards. Six hands to the right.

31:01.860 --> 31:03.032
Turn around.

31:03.195 --> 31:04.447
No, I'll do it this way.

31:05.030 --> 31:06.498
- On my count.
- Amigo...

31:06.656 --> 31:08.158
One.

31:08.283 --> 31:09.284
Two.

31:10.452 --> 31:11.624
Three.

31:13.080 --> 31:14.707
Pull.

31:32.099 --> 31:34.101
(ALL CHEER AND APPLAUD)

31:42.067 --> 31:43.159
(YAWNS)

31:49.991 --> 31:51.664
Good luck with that.

31:51.827 --> 31:53.500
I want food.

31:53.578 --> 31:55.046
Who taught you English?

31:55.622 --> 31:56.669
Sir Ballard.

31:58.375 --> 32:00.127
English and Latin.

32:01.086 --> 32:03.339
Heard he's been here for 25 years.

32:03.422 --> 32:05.470
You won't let him leave.

32:05.841 --> 32:07.309
He must stay here.

32:08.009 --> 32:09.135
What about us?

32:12.222 --> 32:13.769
Pace yourself.

32:13.849 --> 32:15.317
The meals are regular here.

32:15.934 --> 32:17.857
I hope not to stay that long.

32:18.019 --> 32:22.320
I like your thinking, but I suggest
you keep your plans private.

32:22.399 --> 32:26.324
You aren't the first Westerners
to come here looking for black powder.

32:27.195 --> 32:30.665
We'll discuss it tonight. Bring your partner.

32:30.782 --> 32:32.250
How long have you been here?

32:32.367 --> 32:33.414
Always.

32:33.535 --> 32:36.630
I was not five years old when I came here.

32:36.788 --> 32:38.882
I have no other family.

32:39.040 --> 32:40.713
We're the same.

32:40.792 --> 32:43.762
I was given to an army before I can remember.

32:43.837 --> 32:45.134
As a soldier?

32:45.213 --> 32:48.057
Worse. As a gleaner.

32:48.133 --> 32:51.012
Packs of children,
we'd clean the battlefields.

32:51.094 --> 32:53.188
After, when the fighting's over.

32:53.263 --> 32:56.563
I became a page, a pikeman's boy...

32:56.683 --> 32:58.606
For your country?

32:58.727 --> 33:01.401
No. I fought for food.

33:02.355 --> 33:03.948
You fight to eat.

33:04.608 --> 33:06.531
You live long enough, you fight for money.

33:07.444 --> 33:09.822
How many flags do you fight for?

33:11.198 --> 33:12.871
I don't know.

33:14.784 --> 33:17.287
I fought for Harold against the Danes.

33:17.412 --> 33:20.757
I saved a Duke's life.
I fought for him until he died.

33:21.291 --> 33:23.919
Fought for Spain against the Franks.

33:24.252 --> 33:25.925
Fought for the Franks against Boulogne.

33:26.046 --> 33:27.798
I fought for the Pope.

33:29.841 --> 33:31.764
Many flags.

33:35.055 --> 33:37.103
We are not the same.

33:43.563 --> 33:46.783
Meet me on the Wall.
I have something to show you.

33:49.945 --> 33:52.619
He should be careful with her.

33:52.697 --> 33:54.290
She's very powerful here.

33:54.407 --> 33:56.830
Then it is a fair contest.

34:06.336 --> 34:07.462
Come.

34:19.891 --> 34:21.893
- Hmm.
- You wish to try?

34:23.978 --> 34:25.196
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

34:26.773 --> 34:28.650
(WOMAN SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

34:28.817 --> 34:29.864
(ALL CHUCKLE)

34:31.152 --> 34:33.826
(IN ENGLISH)
She says men have so much to teach us.

34:36.116 --> 34:37.583
(GIGGLES)

34:40.495 --> 34:42.168
I don't think that's what she said.

34:42.706 --> 34:44.299
You know what I think?

34:45.250 --> 34:46.376
I think you're afraid.

34:48.962 --> 34:50.839
You said that this morning.

34:51.089 --> 34:52.090
And yet,

34:53.842 --> 34:55.685
- here I am.
- Yes.

34:56.553 --> 34:57.975
Here you are.

35:13.778 --> 35:16.657
Will you jump? Or not?

35:19.618 --> 35:21.541
WILLIAM: These men know what they're doing?

35:21.661 --> 35:22.708
LIN: Wrong question.

35:26.750 --> 35:29.674
Whether or not the cable is attached,

35:30.378 --> 35:32.801
- that is the question.
- (WILLIAM CHUCKLES)

35:34.758 --> 35:36.010
And the answer?

35:36.092 --> 35:37.309
(SPEAKS IN MANDARIN)

35:39.012 --> 35:40.389
(STUTTERS) Xin ren.

35:41.765 --> 35:45.144
(IN ENGLISH)
Xin ren means trust. To have faith.

35:46.227 --> 35:48.776
Here, in this army,

35:49.439 --> 35:52.067
we fight for more than food or money.

35:52.442 --> 35:54.615
We give our lives to something more.

35:56.529 --> 35:58.907
Xin ren is our flag.

35:59.449 --> 36:01.292
Trust in each other.

36:01.868 --> 36:05.418
In all ways, at all times.

36:19.594 --> 36:22.188
Well, that's all well and good,
but I'm not jumping.

36:22.263 --> 36:25.608
I'm alive today because I trust no one.

36:26.768 --> 36:28.941
A man must learn to trust

36:29.104 --> 36:31.482
before he can be trusted.

36:31.606 --> 36:33.574
Then you were right.

36:34.275 --> 36:36.073
We're not the same.

36:38.822 --> 36:40.244
(MEN GRUNTING)

36:42.158 --> 36:44.286
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

36:47.914 --> 36:48.915
(LAUGHS)

36:49.457 --> 36:50.925
(IN ENGLISH) My God!

36:51.000 --> 36:52.092
(CHUCKLES)

36:52.627 --> 36:54.345
A taste, a glimpse.

36:54.462 --> 36:59.263
A few pilfered grains from Strategist
Wang's supply of black powder.

37:00.635 --> 37:04.811
He's mastered the transmutation
of these elements.

37:04.973 --> 37:06.270
People speak of a weapon.

37:06.433 --> 37:08.151
There are many weapons here.

37:08.309 --> 37:09.606
Why have we not seen them?

37:09.686 --> 37:12.906
(SIGHS)
There are many things you have not seen.

37:12.981 --> 37:16.360
And many things you should pray
will not be needed

37:16.526 --> 37:18.904
before the siege is through.

37:21.364 --> 37:23.992
The Tao Tei will return.

37:24.451 --> 37:26.545
When the drums call to battle,

37:27.495 --> 37:31.125
the guards leave their posts
and take their positions on the Wall.

37:31.291 --> 37:33.840
That is our moment.

37:34.627 --> 37:38.681
We want to be riding away
as the battle rages.

37:40.842 --> 37:43.891
And the armory doors? You have keys?

37:44.012 --> 37:45.810
I have black powder.

37:45.889 --> 37:47.857
Enough for several doors.

37:48.433 --> 37:49.855
He brings us in. We get us out.

37:50.560 --> 37:52.688
- (POUNDING ON DOOR)
- (MAN SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

37:55.398 --> 37:58.868
(IN ENGLISH)
As you fought, where was this stone?

37:59.402 --> 38:01.370
In my bag.

38:03.364 --> 38:05.241
Its unseen force is powerful.

38:05.784 --> 38:08.708
I believe this strange stone could help us.

38:10.538 --> 38:12.506
We try everything.

38:13.625 --> 38:15.878
Where are the Tao Tei now?

38:16.002 --> 38:18.425
STRATEGIST WANG: The mountains, regrouping.

38:19.547 --> 38:21.675
Where do they come from?

38:22.217 --> 38:24.390
About 20 centuries ago,

38:24.928 --> 38:29.308
there was an emperor whose greed
brought deep suffering to all of China.

38:29.432 --> 38:32.686
The heavens sent the meteor
that struck Gouwu Mountain,

38:32.852 --> 38:36.106
turning it green and releasing the Tao Tei.

38:36.272 --> 38:40.197
From that day on,
the Tao Tei rise every 60 years

38:40.360 --> 38:43.113
to scourge the north of China.

38:43.279 --> 38:48.911
They come to remind us of what happens
when greed is unchecked.

38:49.077 --> 38:52.581
They eat anything, alive or dead,

38:52.747 --> 38:54.875
and take food to their queen.

38:55.041 --> 38:58.261
She depends on her soldiers to feed her.

38:58.419 --> 39:03.141
Only with the food they provide
is she able to multiply.

39:05.218 --> 39:10.475
The capital, and its two million people,
is only 800 li away.

39:11.391 --> 39:14.315
If the Tao Tei ever had
that much nourishment,

39:14.477 --> 39:17.777
no corner of the world would be safe.

39:18.439 --> 39:19.782
You can't hunt them?

39:19.899 --> 39:21.151
Men try.

39:21.609 --> 39:22.656
They disappear.

39:23.278 --> 39:25.531
We never find their bones.

39:25.613 --> 39:30.119
(SOLDIER SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

39:47.677 --> 39:49.805
(SHAO SPEAKING)

40:21.794 --> 40:23.296
(TAO TEI GROWLING)

40:47.070 --> 40:48.697
(SNARLING)

40:49.989 --> 40:51.787
(SOLDIERS MARCHING)

41:06.673 --> 41:08.425
(GROWLS)

41:11.094 --> 41:13.563
- (SCREAMING)
- (SCREECHING)

41:31.864 --> 41:33.741
(INDISTINCT WHISPERING)

41:46.963 --> 41:47.964
(CRIES SOFTLY)

41:49.257 --> 41:50.759
(GROANING)

42:57.158 --> 42:58.159
(THUDS)

42:59.660 --> 43:01.662
(DRUMS BEATING)

43:20.348 --> 43:22.442
(MAN SINGING)

43:44.789 --> 43:46.632
(ALL SINGING)

44:14.527 --> 44:16.154
(IN ENGLISH)
This is envoy Shen from the palace.

44:16.279 --> 44:19.829
He has brought important records
to help with the coming battle.

44:21.576 --> 44:23.874
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

44:23.995 --> 44:26.418
(IN ENGLISH) A 900-year-old battle report.

44:26.914 --> 44:29.508
- (CONTINUES IN MANDARIN)
- BALLARD: (IN ENGLISH) At the Hansha gates,

44:29.625 --> 44:32.674
three beasts mounted the Wall.

44:32.879 --> 44:36.600
They killed many men as they went forward.

44:36.757 --> 44:40.352
Then, by the grace of the ancient gods,

44:40.511 --> 44:42.764
the beasts stopped...

44:43.806 --> 44:45.228
(READING IN MANDARIN)

44:45.683 --> 44:48.937
...and sat peacefully as we slaughtered them.

44:49.020 --> 44:52.115
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

44:52.231 --> 44:56.611
(IN ENGLISH) At the Hansha Gate,
was a magnet just like this one.

44:56.694 --> 45:01.416
I believe that magnet was the reason
that two of you Westerners

45:01.490 --> 45:03.584
killed the Tao Tei so easily.

45:04.452 --> 45:08.002
I believe the magnet makes the Tao Tei deaf.

45:08.623 --> 45:11.547
Without instruction, they fall still.

45:14.420 --> 45:15.797
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

45:15.922 --> 45:17.048
(IN ENGLISH) How can we be sure?

45:18.799 --> 45:19.891
Why not try it?

45:21.427 --> 45:22.644
Capture a Tao Tei.

45:22.803 --> 45:23.975
See if it works.

45:24.055 --> 45:25.147
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

45:26.641 --> 45:27.642
LIN: (IN ENGLISH) How?

45:27.767 --> 45:29.769
No net is strong enough.

45:29.894 --> 45:32.067
Hunt them. Like a whale.

45:32.647 --> 45:34.240
You know what that is.

45:34.315 --> 45:35.362
Uh... A water beast.

45:35.983 --> 45:39.157
Hundred times the size of a Tao Tei.

45:39.237 --> 45:43.333
A spear that grabs.
Hook the bone. Pull them up.

45:43.407 --> 45:44.875
(STRATEGIST WANG SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

45:47.912 --> 45:49.710
(IN ENGLISH) I've seen it done in Spain.

45:49.830 --> 45:53.630
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

45:54.627 --> 45:56.675
(IN ENGLISH) What the hell are you doing?

45:56.837 --> 45:58.384
We need to be free when the attack comes.

45:58.464 --> 45:59.886
How many chances do you think we will get?

46:02.760 --> 46:06.264
Be injured. Be missing. Be a coward.

46:06.347 --> 46:07.974
Get out of this.

46:09.225 --> 46:10.522
We did enough.

46:20.569 --> 46:21.946
(MAN SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

47:11.579 --> 47:12.796
(WHIRRING)

47:20.671 --> 47:21.718
(BOWL SHATTERS)

48:03.964 --> 48:04.965
TOVAR: (IN ENGLISH) He'll be here.

48:05.049 --> 48:07.222
When? When it's over?

48:07.301 --> 48:09.053
We start and he will find us.

48:09.136 --> 48:10.183
Start?

48:10.304 --> 48:11.977
We're jumping off a cliff here.

48:12.640 --> 48:15.985
I have everything. Powder, tools, maps.

48:16.102 --> 48:18.150
It's all hidden and arranged along the route.

48:18.312 --> 48:22.196
Once we start, there's no going back.

48:35.162 --> 48:36.664
(METAL CREAKING)

48:57.184 --> 48:59.437
- (TAO TEI SCREECHES)
- (SOLDIER 1 SCREAMING)

48:59.895 --> 49:01.147
(SOLDIER 2 SCREAMING)

49:04.900 --> 49:06.243
(GROWLING)

49:08.654 --> 49:10.122
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

49:10.197 --> 49:11.540
(SOLDIERS RESPOND)

49:24.712 --> 49:26.385
(SOLDIERS RESPOND)

49:28.048 --> 49:29.300
(SOLDIERS GRUNTING)

49:35.431 --> 49:36.933
(ALL SPEAKING)

49:37.433 --> 49:38.855
(TAO TEI SCREECHING)

49:41.520 --> 49:43.272
(SOLDIERS GRUNTING)

49:51.864 --> 49:53.332
(SOLDIERS SCREAMING)

50:06.545 --> 50:08.388
- (IN ENGLISH) I'll find him.
- Forget him.

50:08.547 --> 50:11.266
He'd rather die trying to impress
the new general

50:11.383 --> 50:16.059
than grab the key to every counting
room and brothel in the world.

50:16.722 --> 50:18.770
Good God, man. The time is now!

50:18.849 --> 50:20.567
I can't go without him.

50:20.684 --> 50:22.061
More the spoils for us!

50:22.144 --> 50:24.146
We need his bow!

50:27.733 --> 50:28.780
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

50:30.611 --> 50:31.737
(SOLDIER SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

50:52.383 --> 50:53.475
(STRAINING)

50:56.554 --> 50:57.555
(MAN GRUNTING)

50:58.305 --> 50:59.306
(SCREECHING)

51:04.728 --> 51:05.980
(WHIMPERING)

51:31.672 --> 51:32.798
(WHIMPERING)

51:47.813 --> 51:50.066
- (IN ENGLISH) No, no, no. Stop!
- (SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

51:50.190 --> 51:51.442
WILLIAM: (IN ENGLISH)
There's too much tension.

51:51.525 --> 51:52.993
Chain will break.

51:53.068 --> 51:54.661
That way. That way.

51:54.737 --> 51:55.989
- Let him run!
- (SPEAKS IN MANDARIN)

51:56.572 --> 51:58.199
(SCREECHING AND WHIMPERING)

51:59.908 --> 52:01.410
(IN ENGLISH) Stop! Stop!

52:01.535 --> 52:03.879
We need longer
for the sleeping potion to work.

52:04.538 --> 52:06.006
(SCREECHING)

52:08.542 --> 52:09.543
That way. That way.

52:11.086 --> 52:14.090
We need to isolate it.
Separate it from the others.

52:14.214 --> 52:15.386
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

52:15.466 --> 52:16.809
(SOLDIER SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)

52:28.646 --> 52:30.148
(TAO TEI SCREECHING)

52:31.732 --> 52:34.827
STRATEGIST WANG: (IN ENGLISH)
The chain won't hold much longer!

52:35.402 --> 52:36.699
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

52:45.162 --> 52:46.209
LIN: (IN ENGLISH) William, wait.

52:46.288 --> 52:48.256
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

52:49.917 --> 52:53.137
(IN ENGLISH)
These arrows will scream as the Tao Tei run.

52:54.713 --> 52:55.760
Aim for the sound.

53:07.434 --> 53:08.856
(SOLDIER SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

53:20.823 --> 53:22.200
(ARROWS REVERBERATING)

53:33.293 --> 53:34.510
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

53:36.964 --> 53:38.511
(TAO TEI GROWLING SOFTLY)

53:41.635 --> 53:43.103
(CONTINUES GROWLING)

53:49.852 --> 53:51.274
(CHAINS CLANKING)

53:52.146 --> 53:53.272
(GRUNTS)

53:55.441 --> 53:57.239
- (CHAINS CLANKING)
- (WILLIAM GRUNTING)

53:57.568 --> 53:58.820
(MAN SPEAKING)

53:58.986 --> 54:00.738
(CHAINS RATTLING)

54:08.704 --> 54:10.001
(ARROW WHOOSHING)

54:12.624 --> 54:13.841
(TAO TEI SCREECHING)

54:15.711 --> 54:17.509
(GRUNTING)

54:18.172 --> 54:19.970
(BOTH PANTING)

54:20.674 --> 54:23.427
(IN ENGLISH)
I'm only saving you so I can kill you myself.

54:25.888 --> 54:27.231
Grab an ax, we're fighting blind.

54:34.730 --> 54:36.323
(ARROW WHOOSHING SOFTLY)

54:36.815 --> 54:38.863
- (WHISPERS) Not yet.
- I know what to do!

54:40.235 --> 54:41.862
(ARROW WHOOSHING)

55:04.426 --> 55:05.598
(SCREECHES)

55:09.181 --> 55:10.182
The fire's not holding them back.

55:11.058 --> 55:12.401
Die well, brother.

55:19.483 --> 55:20.655
What the hell are you doing?

55:20.734 --> 55:21.906
She's listening.

55:22.152 --> 55:23.825
(ARROWS WHOOSHING)

55:24.488 --> 55:26.490
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

55:26.865 --> 55:28.708
(SOLDIER SPEAKING)

55:37.417 --> 55:39.169
(SOLDIER SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

55:55.769 --> 55:57.146
(EXPLOSIONS)

56:13.745 --> 56:15.213
(PANTING)

56:17.958 --> 56:19.631
(CHAIN CLANKING)

56:28.010 --> 56:29.853
(SOLDIERS SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

56:35.684 --> 56:36.685
(PANTING)

56:47.905 --> 56:49.407
(MAN SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)

56:51.450 --> 56:52.667
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

57:00.751 --> 57:02.173
(WILLIAM SIGHS)

57:03.337 --> 57:04.509
(IN ENGLISH) Did it work?

57:04.588 --> 57:07.182
Yes. The beast was captured.

57:08.592 --> 57:10.219
(GROANS) My friend...

57:10.510 --> 57:12.183
He was unharmed.

57:22.689 --> 57:25.192
Why did you go over the Wall?

57:25.734 --> 57:26.951
(SIGHING)

57:30.197 --> 57:31.494
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

57:33.283 --> 57:34.876
(IN ENGLISH) Did I say it right?

57:38.956 --> 57:40.208
Thank you.

57:46.880 --> 57:48.473
Black powder.

57:50.133 --> 57:52.227
It is a terrible weapon.

57:53.428 --> 57:56.898
It would be better if you had never seen it.

58:01.395 --> 58:04.365
I know very little of the outside world.

58:05.148 --> 58:06.525
But it seems to me,

58:06.608 --> 58:10.078
the greed of men is not that different
from the Tao Tei.

58:11.071 --> 58:12.573
Is that true?

58:13.907 --> 58:16.535
The strong take what they want.

58:27.504 --> 58:29.927
Forget what you have seen.

58:39.683 --> 58:41.481
- (TAO TEI GROWLING)
- (CAGE RATTLING)

59:04.916 --> 59:06.008
(GROWLS SOFTLY)

59:06.626 --> 59:07.718
(STOPS GROWLING)

59:08.462 --> 59:09.463
(SIGHS)

59:18.930 --> 59:20.147
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

59:52.380 --> 59:53.427
Hmm?

59:54.466 --> 59:56.343
(IN ENGLISH)
You're much braver than they think.

01:00:25.038 --> 01:00:26.631
You wounded?

01:00:29.459 --> 01:00:31.052
I was looking for you.

01:00:31.962 --> 01:00:33.134
To say thank you.

01:00:33.463 --> 01:00:34.555
(SCOFFS)

01:00:39.219 --> 01:00:40.721
TOVAR: You feel good, huh?

01:00:41.972 --> 01:00:44.145
Maybe you sing a little song, eh?

01:00:45.267 --> 01:00:46.940
I will join you.

01:00:47.435 --> 01:00:50.234
We can sing together
how you saved the grateful chinos.

01:00:50.355 --> 01:00:52.778
You saw what happened
out there and that's what you say?

01:00:52.899 --> 01:00:53.991
I see black powder.

01:00:55.819 --> 01:00:57.071
I see a man forget his friends.

01:00:57.737 --> 01:00:59.705
The black powder's not going anywhere.

01:00:59.781 --> 01:01:01.875
What goes nowhere is you.

01:01:05.662 --> 01:01:07.960
You'll never get what you want from this.

01:01:08.957 --> 01:01:11.426
You think they see you as some kind of hero?

01:01:11.751 --> 01:01:13.594
A man of virtue?

01:01:14.379 --> 01:01:18.592
Maybe you can fool them,
but I know what you are.

01:01:19.593 --> 01:01:22.267
You know what you are.

01:01:23.180 --> 01:01:24.648
A thief,

01:01:25.223 --> 01:01:26.566
a liar,

01:01:28.852 --> 01:01:30.274
and a killer.

01:01:32.689 --> 01:01:37.068
And you can never undo the things you
have done, and you will never be anything.

01:01:38.695 --> 01:01:40.447
(GRUNTS)

01:01:45.827 --> 01:01:47.454
Good to see you again, amigo.

01:01:55.045 --> 01:01:57.514
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

01:01:58.048 --> 01:01:59.300
(SOLDIER SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

01:02:08.642 --> 01:02:10.440
- (IN ENGLISH) Nothing?
- No.

01:02:10.518 --> 01:02:11.770
How do you know he won't betray us?

01:02:11.853 --> 01:02:12.979
I don't.

01:02:13.063 --> 01:02:14.815
They'll kill him.
They'll kill him no matter what.

01:02:14.898 --> 01:02:16.866
The time they spend killing him

01:02:17.984 --> 01:02:20.157
is time they are not chasing us.

01:03:02.320 --> 01:03:05.369
Careful with that. There's powder here.

01:03:17.544 --> 01:03:19.046
Tovar. (SIGHS)

01:03:50.118 --> 01:03:51.586
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

01:04:18.396 --> 01:04:21.115
(IN ENGLISH)
Have a look. See if it's gone out.

01:04:21.483 --> 01:04:22.609
Is it safe?

01:04:22.776 --> 01:04:24.278
Of course it is.

01:04:36.289 --> 01:04:37.632
(WATER RUNNING)

01:04:45.590 --> 01:04:47.012
(BOTH COUGHING)

01:04:47.467 --> 01:04:49.310
(BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:04:53.139 --> 01:04:55.517
BALLARD: Shake it off, man. To work.

01:04:58.853 --> 01:05:01.197
TOVAR: I thought you said it was safe?

01:05:02.107 --> 01:05:03.700
We're in, aren't we?

01:05:15.537 --> 01:05:16.914
You're here.

01:05:17.497 --> 01:05:19.044
We've come to our senses, eh?

01:05:19.707 --> 01:05:20.959
TOVAR: Ballard has planned well.

01:05:21.042 --> 01:05:22.919
Getting out is easy.

01:05:23.002 --> 01:05:25.346
There's a gate. 20 miles west.

01:05:25.505 --> 01:05:27.348
We dodge the hill tribes.

01:05:28.508 --> 01:05:29.509
We can make it.

01:05:30.885 --> 01:05:32.011
They need us here.

01:05:32.095 --> 01:05:33.893
They need more than us.

01:05:34.848 --> 01:05:36.191
(SIGHS) These people are doomed.

01:05:36.307 --> 01:05:37.354
Don't be a fool.

01:05:37.475 --> 01:05:38.442
I've been a fool.

01:05:38.518 --> 01:05:40.270
I'm done with it.

01:05:40.854 --> 01:05:42.197
Brother, please.

01:05:43.356 --> 01:05:45.358
We've been fighting for nothing.

01:05:46.192 --> 01:05:47.489
For greed.

01:05:48.027 --> 01:05:51.247
Amigo, after all the blood,

01:05:51.322 --> 01:05:53.825
and cold, and pain,

01:05:53.950 --> 01:05:56.328
with this black powder in our saddle bags,

01:05:56.411 --> 01:05:57.913
we win.

01:05:59.205 --> 01:06:00.422
You come with me.

01:06:02.208 --> 01:06:03.460
I can't do that now.

01:06:05.670 --> 01:06:06.717
Stay and fight.

01:06:08.131 --> 01:06:09.383
William...

01:06:13.928 --> 01:06:15.020
BALLARD: Think he's dead?

01:06:15.096 --> 01:06:17.144
It'd take a lot more than that.

01:06:21.186 --> 01:06:23.564
(STRATEGIST WANG SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

01:07:09.192 --> 01:07:10.444
TOVAR: Come on.

01:07:10.944 --> 01:07:11.991
Hyah.

01:07:29.921 --> 01:07:32.674
- (INDISTINCT MURMURS)
- (TAO TEI SNORING)

01:07:44.435 --> 01:07:45.652
(ALL GASP)

01:08:00.493 --> 01:08:01.836
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

01:08:35.361 --> 01:08:38.205
- (IN ENGLISH) I tried to stop them...
- You dare to speak to me?

01:08:40.198 --> 01:08:41.451
I didn't do this.

01:08:42.035 --> 01:08:45.038
And you came here to trade.

01:08:45.203 --> 01:08:47.046
And you knew nothing of black powder.

01:08:49.207 --> 01:08:51.676
What a fool you must think I am.

01:08:51.752 --> 01:08:54.006
If I was with them, why would I be here?

01:08:54.087 --> 01:08:55.180
I tried to stop them. I tried...

01:08:55.256 --> 01:08:56.553
(SPEAKS IN MANDARIN)

01:08:57.884 --> 01:08:59.261
You lie.

01:09:00.928 --> 01:09:03.022
Some part of you knows that's not true.

01:09:03.096 --> 01:09:08.024
If I were not the General,
I would kill you myself.

01:09:10.063 --> 01:09:11.234
(SOLDIER SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

01:09:52.897 --> 01:09:54.274
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:10:13.167 --> 01:10:14.589
(DOOR LOCKS)

01:10:27.223 --> 01:10:28.975
(IN ENGLISH) Which way, left or right?

01:10:29.642 --> 01:10:32.441
Go up and take a look from the high ground.

01:10:44.490 --> 01:10:45.992
- Hyah!
- (HORSES NEIGHING)

01:10:47.326 --> 01:10:48.418
No!

01:10:48.995 --> 01:10:51.498
No! Bastard!

01:10:54.292 --> 01:10:55.544
(PANTING)

01:11:15.605 --> 01:11:16.857
(EXPLOSIONS)

01:11:27.241 --> 01:11:28.584
(SCREAMING)

01:11:33.623 --> 01:11:35.717
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

01:12:12.787 --> 01:12:14.164
WILLIAM: (IN ENGLISH) What happened?

01:12:17.208 --> 01:12:18.380
What happened?

01:12:18.501 --> 01:12:20.344
We have failed.

01:12:20.503 --> 01:12:22.926
The Tao Tei are in the Kingdom.

01:12:23.506 --> 01:12:26.931
You are free to leave.
Take what you wish and go.

01:12:27.051 --> 01:12:29.099
This was the General's final order.

01:12:29.220 --> 01:12:30.392
Where is she?

01:12:34.976 --> 01:12:36.398
To do what?

01:12:36.477 --> 01:12:37.603
To fight?

01:12:37.728 --> 01:12:39.025
Is there a chance?

01:12:39.146 --> 01:12:40.272
There's only one.

01:12:40.773 --> 01:12:42.775
Kill the Queen.

01:12:42.859 --> 01:12:45.032
Kill the Queen, or we all die.

01:12:46.863 --> 01:12:47.955
Leave.

01:12:48.531 --> 01:12:52.873
Tell the world what you have seen,
and tell them what is coming.

01:13:01.377 --> 01:13:03.220
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

01:13:15.892 --> 01:13:17.519
I'll need my bow.

01:13:21.272 --> 01:13:23.821
If I'm to join you, I'll need my bow.

01:13:29.697 --> 01:13:31.290
(SOLDIER SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

01:13:35.369 --> 01:13:37.417
(IN ENGLISH) He wishes to join us.

01:13:42.501 --> 01:13:44.219
(HORSES NEIGHING)

01:13:45.379 --> 01:13:47.006
(MEN APPROACHING)

01:13:54.847 --> 01:13:55.848
(ALL GASP)

01:13:59.518 --> 01:14:00.610
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

01:14:05.274 --> 01:14:06.617
(SNORING)

01:14:14.116 --> 01:14:15.117
(ALL GASP)

01:14:20.039 --> 01:14:21.666
- (PEOPLE SCREAMING)
- (TAO TEI SCREECHING)

01:14:24.502 --> 01:14:25.628
(CHITTERING)

01:14:34.929 --> 01:14:35.930
(CHITTERING)

01:15:00.287 --> 01:15:01.539
(GRUNTS)

01:15:04.750 --> 01:15:05.842
(GROWLS SOFTLY)

01:15:26.605 --> 01:15:27.697
(MEN LAUGHING)

01:15:31.902 --> 01:15:32.949
(MUFFLED IN ENGLISH) No.

01:15:33.029 --> 01:15:34.030
No.

01:15:38.701 --> 01:15:39.702
No.

01:15:44.582 --> 01:15:45.583
No.

01:15:47.126 --> 01:15:50.130
No, don't throw that thing near fire!

01:15:54.592 --> 01:15:55.935
(EXPLOSIONS)

01:15:58.304 --> 01:15:59.476
(GRUNTS)

01:16:05.978 --> 01:16:07.855
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

01:16:20.201 --> 01:16:21.544
(TAO TEI SCREECHING)

01:16:25.164 --> 01:16:26.461
(MEN SCREAMING)

01:16:48.354 --> 01:16:49.355
(GRUNTING)

01:17:01.367 --> 01:17:02.584
(TAO TEI GROWLING)

01:17:09.375 --> 01:17:10.752
WILLIAM: (IN ENGLISH) Above you!

01:17:19.510 --> 01:17:20.511
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

01:17:24.974 --> 01:17:26.567
(IN ENGLISH) Behind you!

01:17:28.102 --> 01:17:29.399
(TAO TEI SCREECHING)

01:17:37.278 --> 01:17:38.450
(LIN GRUNTS)

01:17:39.155 --> 01:17:40.748
I set you free.

01:17:41.740 --> 01:17:43.083
And here I am.

01:17:44.785 --> 01:17:45.911
There's the Queen!

01:17:50.875 --> 01:17:53.298
They will not attack
while the Queen is feeding.

01:17:53.419 --> 01:17:55.342
We have a chance!

01:17:55.421 --> 01:17:56.513
Hold on!

01:18:04.972 --> 01:18:06.599
(SCREAMING)

01:18:07.975 --> 01:18:09.227
(CLATTERING)

01:18:10.978 --> 01:18:13.697
- (SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)
- (PEOPLE SCREAMING)

01:19:05.908 --> 01:19:07.034
(HORSE SNORTING)

01:19:18.504 --> 01:19:20.347
(IN ENGLISH)
There is an underground canal here.

01:19:20.506 --> 01:19:22.349
WILLIAM: Has it been breached?

01:19:22.424 --> 01:19:23.926
The Tao Tei should all be above ground.

01:19:24.635 --> 01:19:25.852
And the one we captured?

01:19:26.345 --> 01:19:27.346
STRATEGIST WANG: We load it up.

01:19:28.472 --> 01:19:29.815
We feed it.

01:19:29.890 --> 01:19:31.858
And it will return to its Queen.

01:19:32.059 --> 01:19:33.026
Good.

01:19:51.578 --> 01:19:53.046
(HORSES WHINNYING)

01:19:57.626 --> 01:19:59.048
(TAO TEI SCREECHING)

01:20:15.227 --> 01:20:16.228
(MAN YELLS)

01:20:21.150 --> 01:20:22.151
(GRUNTS)

01:20:42.254 --> 01:20:44.552
You'll have one hell of a scar,
but you'll live.

01:20:45.257 --> 01:20:46.258
(LIN SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

01:20:47.718 --> 01:20:49.391
(IN ENGLISH) We'll come back for him.

01:21:03.817 --> 01:21:04.818
(TAO TEI SHRIEKING)

01:21:07.404 --> 01:21:08.872
LIN: They've broken through!

01:21:58.831 --> 01:22:00.833
(TAO TEI BREATHING)

01:22:11.427 --> 01:22:13.521
(GROWLING)

01:22:19.226 --> 01:22:20.227
(SNARLS)

01:22:31.363 --> 01:22:33.991
Patience, William.

01:22:44.209 --> 01:22:45.927
(SNIFFING)

01:22:50.966 --> 01:22:54.061
And it will go to the Queen when it's done?

01:22:54.303 --> 01:22:55.520
It should.

01:22:58.056 --> 01:22:59.103
It will.

01:23:07.983 --> 01:23:08.984
(SHRIEKING)

01:23:11.069 --> 01:23:12.070
Let it in.

01:23:21.121 --> 01:23:22.543
(GROWLING)

01:23:36.136 --> 01:23:37.433
I can get a shot from above.

01:23:38.347 --> 01:23:40.395
(DOOR THUDDING)

01:23:42.476 --> 01:23:44.774
Go! I'll hold them back.

01:24:07.793 --> 01:24:09.295
Wait. Not yet.

01:24:17.886 --> 01:24:18.978
WILLIAM: Hit.

01:24:28.146 --> 01:24:29.113
Go higher.

01:24:29.189 --> 01:24:30.657
I'll get a better shot.

01:24:31.984 --> 01:24:32.985
(GROWLING)

01:24:34.903 --> 01:24:35.904
(CALLING)

01:24:43.954 --> 01:24:44.955
STRATEGIST WANG: General!

01:24:45.038 --> 01:24:46.335
It's up to you now!

01:25:28.665 --> 01:25:29.666
(GROWLS)

01:25:30.834 --> 01:25:31.835
(CALLING)

01:25:39.217 --> 01:25:40.844
We have one black powder weapon left.

01:25:40.927 --> 01:25:42.395
Give me the spear.

01:25:44.556 --> 01:25:46.024
I've trained for this my whole life.

01:25:48.101 --> 01:25:49.398
(SPEAKS IN MANDARIN)

01:25:53.065 --> 01:25:54.191
(IN ENGLISH) I'll get you the shot.

01:26:03.659 --> 01:26:05.627
(ALL SNARLING)

01:26:31.019 --> 01:26:32.020
(BOTH GRUNT)

01:26:35.065 --> 01:26:36.066
(LIN GRUNTS)

01:26:40.320 --> 01:26:41.617
I've got you.

01:26:42.781 --> 01:26:44.783
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:26:54.334 --> 01:26:55.335
(CLATTERING)

01:27:59.524 --> 01:28:01.618
So, how's life without me?

01:28:02.861 --> 01:28:04.283
A little slow.

01:28:07.532 --> 01:28:09.159
You're a hero after all.

01:28:09.701 --> 01:28:10.953
Well, it looks that way.

01:28:11.036 --> 01:28:13.380
You seem pleased with yourself.

01:28:13.455 --> 01:28:15.878
And what are they giving you
for all of your troubles?

01:28:16.041 --> 01:28:17.042
A bag of gold?

01:28:17.626 --> 01:28:19.799
A victory parade along the top of the Wall?

01:28:20.378 --> 01:28:22.301
All the black powder I can carry.

01:28:22.881 --> 01:28:25.600
And a cavalry escort to get me home safely.

01:28:26.718 --> 01:28:28.061
Well, congratulations.

01:28:28.136 --> 01:28:29.979
Thank you.

01:28:30.055 --> 01:28:33.355
So what is this?
You're here to rub my nose in it?

01:28:33.558 --> 01:28:34.980
Well, would you blame me?

01:28:35.060 --> 01:28:37.438
The last time I saw you,
you left me for dead.

01:28:37.562 --> 01:28:39.485
And the time before that, I saved your life.

01:28:39.564 --> 01:28:40.907
True.

01:28:43.235 --> 01:28:45.829
You know, the Emperor gave me a choice.

01:28:45.904 --> 01:28:48.123
I could take the black powder,

01:28:48.281 --> 01:28:50.625
or I could take you.

01:28:52.452 --> 01:28:54.420
Please tell me you chose the powder?

01:29:01.670 --> 01:29:03.388
I don't even know you anymore.

01:29:04.005 --> 01:29:05.006
(CHUCKLES)

01:29:06.091 --> 01:29:07.718
The horses are saddled and waiting.

01:29:07.801 --> 01:29:10.099
Best we ride before nightfall.

01:29:15.600 --> 01:29:17.273
I'll be inside.

01:29:17.352 --> 01:29:19.229
Don't leave without me.

01:29:29.948 --> 01:29:31.120
I came to say goodbye.

01:29:33.451 --> 01:29:36.705
I understand congratulations are in order.

01:29:36.872 --> 01:29:39.125
General of the northwest territory.

01:29:39.291 --> 01:29:40.964
That's quite an honor.

01:29:43.461 --> 01:29:45.589
Seems you've made your choice.

01:29:45.714 --> 01:29:46.806
Him?

01:29:46.965 --> 01:29:49.844
Believe me, I'm already thinking about
trading him back for the powder.

01:29:50.010 --> 01:29:51.978
- (CHUCKLES)
- TOVAR: I heard that.

01:29:57.642 --> 01:30:00.771
Perhaps we were both wrong.

01:30:01.313 --> 01:30:03.987
We are more similar than I thought.

01:30:09.654 --> 01:30:11.372
Thank you, General.

01:30:27.130 --> 01:30:28.177
(HORSE GRUNTS)

01:30:37.307 --> 01:30:39.355
Are you sure you don't want to go back?

01:30:40.018 --> 01:30:41.019
Of course I do.

01:30:42.187 --> 01:30:44.690
I just don't trust you
to make it out of here alone.

01:30:44.773 --> 01:30:45.774
(TOVAR LAUGHS)

